      • createInstance

        public static java.lang.Object createInstance​(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                                              ArgumentResult... parameters)
                                       throws java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException,
                                              java.lang.InstantiationException,
                                              java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        Creates an instance of the specified class with the arguments' results as parameters Uses a special method to locate constructor with primitive type of parameter with comparing primitive type to its non-primitive pair

        NOTE: To be able to create the instance, the parameters count, order and type must match with one of the constructors in the requested class For more information about the exceptions see Constructor.newInstance(Object...)

        Parameters:
        clazz - is the requested type
        parameters - the results of the arguments
        Returns:
        the instance of the class
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - when the clazz doesn't contain constructor that matches with parameters count, type and order
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
        java.lang.InstantiationException
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException
